      "results": [
        {
          "ruleId": "review-note",
          "ruleIndex": 0,
          "kind": "informational",
          "level": "none",
          "guid": "mrx3zfl8w64w1q75",
          "message": {
            "text": "**Why the app-switch glides are pure `scale()` with a directional `transform-origin` (no translate).** Round 2's \"terminal suddenly disappears\" transitions had two stacked causes, both proven from the emitted SVG:\n\n1. **Baked-relative composition.** domotion element animations compose with the transform an element was CAPTURED with. Round 2 parked windows via page CSS, so the outgoing window was captured already-parked and the config's `front → park` tween re-applied the park on top — teleporting it off-stage at the cut. Fix: capture every window untransformed; glides live only in the config.\n\n2. **Cross-frame `cull-N` class collision (domotion bug, filed upstream).** The viewBox culler reads only an animation's *translate* component (scale ignored) against each CHILD's static bbox, and numbers its visibility classes `cull-0, cull-1, …` PER FRAME. With several switch frames emitting windows, later frames' `@keyframes cull-0` clobber earlier frames'. Concretely: frame 10's editor code runs whose right edge sat left of x=250 got an exit-window named `cull-0`, and frame 36's end-card enter-window (visible only from 91.58% of the loop) was ALSO named `cull-0` and won — so \"import\", \"const\", line numbers, and the tab title vanished for the whole session (the missing-text screenshots in the ticket round-3 iteration).\n\nA `scale(1) ↔ scale(0.12)` tween moves no bbox in the culler's translate-only math → zero cull classes emitted (verified: `cull-` count in the final SVG is 0), while `transform-origin: 8% 92%` (etc.) still yields the diagonal shrink-toward-a-corner app-switch path. Windows tuck INSIDE the stage, covered by the opaque front window (z6 over z5), and return from the same corner they exited to.\n",
            "markdown": "**Why the app-switch glides are pure `scale()` with a directional `transform-origin` (no translate).** Round 2's \"terminal suddenly disappears\" transitions had two stacked causes, both proven from the emitted SVG:\n\n1. **Baked-relative composition.** domotion element animations compose with the transform an element was CAPTURED with. Round 2 parked windows via page CSS, so the outgoing window was captured already-parked and the config's `front → park` tween re-applied the park on top — teleporting it off-stage at the cut. Fix: capture every window untransformed; glides live only in the config.\n\n2. **Cross-frame `cull-N` class collision (domotion bug, filed upstream).** The viewBox culler reads only an animation's *translate* component (scale ignored) against each CHILD's static bbox, and numbers its visibility classes `cull-0, cull-1, …` PER FRAME. With several switch frames emitting windows, later frames' `@keyframes cull-0` clobber earlier frames'. Concretely: frame 10's editor code runs whose right edge sat left of x=250 got an exit-window named `cull-0`, and frame 36's end-card enter-window (visible only from 91.58% of the loop) was ALSO named `cull-0` and won — so \"import\", \"const\", line numbers, and the tab title vanished for the whole session (the missing-text screenshots in the ticket round-3 iteration).\n\nA `scale(1) ↔ scale(0.12)` tween moves no bbox in the culler's translate-only math → zero cull classes emitted (verified: `cull-` count in the final SVG is 0), while `transform-origin: 8% 92%` (etc.) still yields the diagonal shrink-toward-a-corner app-switch path. Windows tuck INSIDE the stage, covered by the opaque front window (z6 over z5), and return from the same corner they exited to.\n"
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "site/scripts/demo-captures/gen-getting-started.mjs"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 49,
                  "endLine": 70,
                  "snippet": {
                    "text": "const __dirname = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n\nconst CUT = { type: 'cut', duration: 0 };\n\n// --- app-switch glides (baked-relative: all windows captured at front) ----\n// Pure scale() tweens; the transform-origin picks the corner the window\n// shrinks toward / grows from, giving the diagonal app-switch path with no\n// translate for the viewBox culler to act on (see rule 2 above). A window\n// RETURNS from the same corner it tucked into.\nconst FRONT = 'scale(1)';\nconst TUCK = 'scale(0.12)';\nconst ORIGIN_BL = '8% 92%';    // editor + terminal tuck: bottom-left\nconst ORIGIN_BR = '92% 90%';   // browser tuck: bottom-right\nconst ORIGIN_B = '50% 95%';    // new-window pops: bottom-center\nconst EASE_SWITCH = 'cubic-bezier(0.645,0.045,0.355,1)';\nconst glide = (selector, from, to, origin, opts = {}) => ({\n  selector,\n  property: 'transform',\n  from,\n  to,\n  duration: opts.duration ?? 480,\n  easing: opts.easing ?? EASE_SWITCH,"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "properties": {
            "tags": [
              "rationale"
            ]
          },
          "workItemUris": [
            "KF-371"
          ],
          "partialFingerprints": {
            "prNoteAnchor/v1": "dcf3b5199311f04f7586f90a8ce2b6d7"
          }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "review-note",
          "ruleIndex": 0,
          "kind": "informational",
          "level": "none",
          "guid": "mrx3zfs2nf16pvhf",
          "message": {
            "text": "**One animation per element per frame.** `data-domotion-anim` is a single attribute set per matched element, so a frame's second `animations` entry on the same selector silently overwrites the first (round 2's click-5 frame lost its click-dip pop this way — `anim-f28a0` was absent from the emitted SVG while `f28a1` was present). The click-5 frame now uses ONE merged pop (0.93 → 1.07). The tags also persist on the live page into every later frame's capture; that persistence is load-bearing here — it is what holds a tucked window at its parked scale for the rest of the session.",
            "markdown": "**One animation per element per frame.** `data-domotion-anim` is a single attribute set per matched element, so a frame's second `animations` entry on the same selector silently overwrites the first (round 2's click-5 frame lost its click-dip pop this way — `anim-f28a0` was absent from the emitted SVG while `f28a1` was present). The click-5 frame now uses ONE merged pop (0.93 → 1.07). The tags also persist on the live page into every later frame's capture; that persistence is load-bearing here — it is what holds a tucked window at its parked scale for the rest of the session."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "site/scripts/demo-captures/gen-getting-started.mjs"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 148,
                  "endLine": 152,
                  "snippet": {
                    "text": "    { type: 'wait', ms: 120 },\n  ],\n  animations: [\n    // NOTE: one animation per element per frame — a second entry targeting\n    // #counter-btn would overwrite the first's data-domotion-anim tag."
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "properties": {
