          }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "review-note",
          "ruleIndex": 0,
          "kind": "informational",
          "level": "none",
          "guid": "mrx3zolmiqj13999",
          "message": {
            "text": "**Push-typing is page-driven per-2-char frames, not overlays.** The mid-line edits (` computed,` into the import; `\"btn\"` → `{cls}`) must SHIFT the text right of the caret as characters land — a typing overlay paints on top of a static capture and cannot reflow it, which is exactly the round-3 'edits overlay rather than push' complaint. Considered domotion's `typeResample` (real per-keystroke re-capture) but it only drives form fields (input/textarea), not rich syntax-colored markup. So `window.ins(k)`/`window.rep(k)` re-render the real line with k plain characters inserted + a block caret, one cut frame per 2 chars (~85 ms/char — brisk real typing). Cost: 8 extra frames ≈ nothing after gzip (the whole 37-frame SVG gzips to ~68 KB, smaller than round 2's 31-frame ~95 KB because glyph dedup compresses repeated editor states well). A domotion feature ticket for first-class rich-text display/editing (the general fix) is filed in the domotion Hot Sheet.",
            "markdown": "**Push-typing is page-driven per-2-char frames, not overlays.** The mid-line edits (` computed,` into the import; `\"btn\"` → `{cls}`) must SHIFT the text right of the caret as characters land — a typing overlay paints on top of a static capture and cannot reflow it, which is exactly the round-3 'edits overlay rather than push' complaint. Considered domotion's `typeResample` (real per-keystroke re-capture) but it only drives form fields (input/textarea), not rich syntax-colored markup. So `window.ins(k)`/`window.rep(k)` re-render the real line with k plain characters inserted + a block caret, one cut frame per 2 chars (~85 ms/char — brisk real typing). Cost: 8 extra frames ≈ nothing after gzip (the whole 37-frame SVG gzips to ~68 KB, smaller than round 2's 31-frame ~95 KB because glyph dedup compresses repeated editor states well). A domotion feature ticket for first-class rich-text display/editing (the general fix) is filed in the domotion Hot Sheet."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "site/scripts/demo-captures/gen-getting-started.mjs"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 156,
                  "endLine": 164,
                  "snippet": {
                    "text": "});\n\n// Page-driven push-typing: k chars landed via window.ins/rep — REAL page\n// text, so everything right of the caret genuinely shifts. ~2 chars per\n// frame reads as brisk real typing at these durations.\nconst pushFrame = (script, dur = 170) => ({\n  continue: true,\n  transition: CUT,\n  actions: [{ type: 'evaluate', script }],"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          ],
